title: Italian baked meatballs
ingredients:
[VEGGIE BASE]
0.5 onion (diced)
2 garlic cloves (minced)

# Marinara Sauce 

[MEATBALLS]
400 g ground beef
(0.5 cup breadcrumbs)
0.3 cup flour
0.25 cup quinoa (already cooked)
1 tbsp garlic powder
1 tbsp Italian seasoning
1 egg

[CHEESE TOPPERS]
2 balls mozzarella (shredded)
60 g shredded gratin cheese
instructions:
Saute VEGGIE BASE. 
Put in bowl to make MEATBALLS.
Mix MEATBALLS & brown them in pan.

Meanwhile, mix # Marinara Sauce (no need to pre-cook) in the baking dish. 
Preheat oven to 200°C.
Place browned MEATBALLS in SAUCE. 
Distribute CHEESE TOPPERS; large dollops & grated cheese randomly tossed on.
Bake in oven for 25 minutes. 

Meanwhile, cook desired SIDE (rice, pasta, or bread)

title: Holiday cheesecake
description: pumpkin + caramel swirl & raspberry + chocolate swirl
ingredients:
# 0.5 cup Salted caramel
# 0.5 cup Raspberry sauce
# Shortbread cheesecake crust

[CREAM]
875 g cream cheese (softened)
0.5 cup sugar
0.3 cup sour cream (softened)
1 tsp vanilla extract
3 eggs

[PUMPKIN CREAM]
(0.75 cup CREAM)
100 g pumpkin puree
2 tsp ginger powder (and/or cinnamon)
0.25 tsp nutmeg

[CHOCOLATE]
80 g chocolate chips
instructions:
If needed, prepare # Salted caramel & # Smooth raspberry sauce.

Adjust the oven rack to the lower-middle position & preheat oven to 175°C.
Prepare # Shortbread cheesecake crust.

[CREAM]
Beat the CREAM mixture (without eggs) on medium speed in a large bowl until creamy. 
Add the eggs one at a time, beating after each addition until just blended.

[PUMPKIN CREAM]
Mix together.

[CHOCOLATE]
Melt chocolate chips, be careful not to burn them.

[ASSEMBLE CAKE]
The cake is composed of layers of CREAM and flavors. Into the crust:
   • spread 1 cm layer of CREAM
   • on half, drop 1 tbsp PUMPKIN CREAM & 0.5 tsp caramel sauce. Do this 3 more times in           
     different areas. Using a knife  or sharp edge swirl the two layers some.
    • on the other half, alternate between dropping 1 tsp RASPBERRY SAUCE & CHOCOLATE. 
      Do this for 10-12 drops. Again swirl together layers.
Repeat the steps above until out of CREAM.

[BAKING]
In another baking dish or roasting pan, put 2 cm of water. Put this dish a level below where the cake where sit.

Bake it for 55-70 minutes or until the center is almost set (still slightly wobbles). 
Let it sit in the open oven for 1 hour.
Refrigerate it for at least 4 hours or overnight.

Use a knife to loosen it from the rim of the springform pan, then remove the rim.
For neat slices, wipe the knife clean and dip into warm water between each slice.

title: Shortbread cheesecake crust
ingredients:
1.25 cups flour
0.75 cup buckwheat flour
0.5 cup flour
180 g butter (melted)
0.25 cup brown sugar
2 eggs
instructions:
Preheat oven to 175°C.

Mix together crust ingredients. 

Press firmly into the bottom and two-thirds up the sides of a 25 cm springform pan. 

Pre-bake for 10 minutes or until lightly golden brown.

title: Raspberry sauce
ingredients:
340 g frozen raspberries
0.3 cup water
1 tbsp starch
instructions:
Add all ingredients. Boil for 5 min.

For a smooth sauce, strain through a mesh strainer to remove seeds. Use spatula to improve liquid separation by repeatedly brushing over bottom of the strainer.

For a chunk sauce, mash or blend berries.

title: Salted caramel
ingredients:
0.75 cup sugar
6 tbsp butter (chunked)
0.5 cup 30% fat cream
1 tsp salt
instructions:
MEASURE all ingredients first! No time during to do. Throughout the recipe, stir constantly, unless it says otherwise.

Heat sugar over medium heat. It eventually melts into an amber-colored liquid.

Add the butter one chunk at a time. After its all combined, cook for 2 minutes without stirring.

Temporarily remove the pan from heat & add in heavy cream. Return to heat. 
Do not stir & allow to boil for 1 minute. 

Remove from heat and stir in the salt. 

Allow to cool down before using. It will solidify in the refrigerator. Reheat in the microwave or on the stove to desired consistency.

Put any leftovers in small containers in the freezer.
